They're playing the second-string.

63
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:10,040
That's great for us.

64
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:14,050
Just as Kine says, what's important in this game isn't how we play.

65
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:17,300
What's important is that we win, no matter what tactics we use.

66
00:05:18,030 --> 00:05:18,500


67
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:21,150
Bow !

68
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:22,700
Pleased to play with you !

69
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,800
Team

70
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,800
Meiwa Ichi

71
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,800
Senkawa

72
00:05:24,460 --> 00:05:28,650
They let us take the field first, even though we're the visitor.


73
00:05:28,650 --> 00:05:30,800
It's all great for us.

74
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,900
I thought I asked you 
not to hold back on us.

75
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:56,230
Well, it's way too cruel to play
the first-string from the start.

76
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:59,310
It would be a problem if you lose to us.

77
00:06:00,650 --> 00:06:04,790
Oh, stop kidding. They aren't 
your usual second-string players.

78
00:06:04,790 --> 00:06:08,260
They're second-string on Meiwa's team, 
which is famed for its deep roster.

79
00:06:08,260 --> 00:06:13,000
